2018. i haven’t been very active on here throughout 2017. i’ve had to admit something to myself. i’ve had too high expectations of myself this year. too many excuses in my head for why i haven’t been out shooting. ‘does this pic match that pic color wise in my organized feed?’, ‘how do i create an organized feed i like?’, ‘i need to outdo myself in every new post’ are only some of those thoughts that’s been running through my head. i haven’t felt motivated. i’ve come to understand that for me to start shooting again i need to stop worrying about these things. what made me happy before was taking photos while making memories. not pleasing anyone but myself. 4 months ago i moved to valby, copenhagen so why not start it off with showing my new neighborhood. expect more snapshots like this on this channel📸 can’t wait to see what this year has in store. here’s to 2018🥂

the swedish attack on copenhagen 11 febuary 1659. was the danish defence of copenhagen in the second karl-gustav war. as a follow of the treaty of roskilde 1658 attacked the swedish king karl x gustav copenhagen from the south in amager and valby. the swedish siege lasted from the 7th august to the 11th febuary 1659. the netherlands helped denmark in the war, becuase they wanted to stop the swedish aggression. the danish army had 10.000 soldiers including the kings royal guard, the civil defence, and 2500 dutch soldiers. there was also over 600 civilians from copenhagen defending the city.(students, and craftsmen) the swedish had 10.000 trained soldiers. the danish king insisted to be in the city, and said: "jeg vil dø i min rede!" ("i will die in my nest!" the battle resulted in a danish victory. the danish lost 14 men. the swedish lost 1700 men. ---------------------------------- thedanishhistory danishhistory scandinavia denmark history swedishhistory napoleonicwars 1659 historybuff historypage
